### Test Data Categories

#### Contract Test Data
- **Location**: `src/test/resources/contract-test-data/`
- **Purpose**: Real payloads for command-to-event validation
- **Organization**: Grouped by command endpoint and scenario
- **Validation**: Must be valid against corresponding JSON schemas

#### Scenario Test Data
- **Location**: `src/test/resources/scenarios/` (in scenario-test module)
- **Purpose**: Multi-step business scenarios
- **Organization**: Sequential steps with expected outcomes
- **Format**: Numbered files showing workflow progression

#### Stub Data (Existing)
- **Location**: `src/test/resources/stub-data/` directories
- **Purpose**: Mock external service responses
- **Format**: JSON files matching expected schemas
- **Usage**: Use in unit and integration tests

#### Mock Data (Existing)
- **Location**: `src/test/resources/mock-data/` in [listing-common](mdc:listing-common)
- **Purpose**: Shared mock data across modules
- **Examples**: Azure service responses, external API stubs

## Multi-Layer Test Execution

### Test Execution Commands

```bash
# Daily development - Fast unit tests only (default)
mvn test

# CI Pipeline - Contract tests for command-to-event validation
mvn test -Pcontract-test

# Full integration validation - Complete stack testing
mvn test -Pintegration-test -pl listing-integration-test -DINTEGRATION_HOST_KEY=localhost

# Comprehensive scenario validation - On-demand only
mvn test -Pscenario-test -pl listing-scenario-test

# All tests (for release validation)
mvn test -Pall-tests
```

### Maven Profiles Configuration

The project uses Maven profiles to control test execution:

```xml
<profiles>
    <!-- Default: Unit tests only -->
    <profile>
        <id>unit-test</id>
        <activation><activeByDefault>true</activeByDefault></activation>
        <properties>
            <excludedGroups>integration,scenario,contract</excludedGroups>
        </properties>
    </profile>
    
    <!-- Contract tests for CI -->
    <profile>
        <id>contract-test</id>
        <properties>
            <groups>contract</groups>
        </properties>
    </profile>
    
    <!-- Integration tests -->
    <profile>
        <id>integration-test</id>
        <properties>
            <groups>integration</groups>
        </properties>
    </profile>
    
    <!-- Scenario tests (on-demand) -->
    <profile>
        <id>scenario-test</id>
        <properties>
            <groups>scenario</groups>
        </properties>
    </profile>
</profiles>
```

## Testing Best Practices by Layer

### Unit Testing (Fast, Isolated)
```java
@Test
public void shouldProcessCommandSuccessfully() {
    // Given: Minimal setup with mocks
    Command command = createTestCommand();
    when(mockRepository.save(any())).thenReturn(savedEntity);
    
    // When: Execute single method
    CommandResult result = handler.handle(command);
    
    // Then: Verify behavior
    assertThat(result.isSuccess()).isTrue();
    verify(mockRepository).save(any(Entity.class));
}
```

### Contract Testing (Real Serialization)
```java
@Test
@Category(ContractTest.class)
public void shouldGenerateExpectedEventsForRealPayload() {
    // Given: Real JSON payload from test data
    JsonEnvelope command = loadTestCommand("adhoc_hearing_creation.json");
    
    // When: Execute through real handler (mock external services only)
    List<JsonEnvelope> events = executeCommandAndCaptureEvents(command);
    
    // Then: Verify event structure and payload mapping
    assertThat(events, hasSize(2));
    assertEventPresent(events, "hearing-listed-event");
    JsonEnvelope event = findEvent(events, "hearing-listed-event");
    assertJsonSchema(event, "hearing-listed-event.schema.json");
    assertFieldMapping(command, event, "hearingId", "courtCentreId");
}
```

### Integration Testing (Full Stack)
```java
@Test
@Category(IntegrationTest.class)
public void shouldProcessEndToEndScenario() {
    // Given: Real payload and full application context
    String requestBody = loadTestData("scenarios/adhoc_hearing_creation.json");
    
    // When: Call actual REST endpoint
    Response response = given()
        .contentType(JSON)
        .body(requestBody)
        .post("/api/commands/list-court-hearing");
    
    // Then: Verify response and side effects
    response.then().statusCode(200);
    await().atMost(5, SECONDS).until(() -> 
        eventStore.getEventsForStream(hearingId).size() >= 2);
}
```

### Scenario Testing (Business Workflows)
```java
@Test
@Category(ScenarioTest.class)
public void shouldCompleteAdhocHearingCreationWorkflow() {
    // Given: Multi-step scenario data
    ScenarioData scenario = loadScenario("adhoc-hearing-creation");
    
    // When: Execute scenario steps
    ScenarioResult result = scenarioExecutor.execute(scenario);
    
    // Then: Verify complete workflow outcome
    assertThat(result.isSuccessful()).isTrue();
    assertThat(result.getGeneratedEvents()).hasSize(3);
    assertThat(result.getFinalState()).matches(scenario.getExpectedOutcome());
}
```

